{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 {\b 3. Typography}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Primary (UI/Marketing):} {\b Inter} (Bold/ExtraBold).\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab Used for headlines and primary brand text.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Secondary (Content):} {\b Inter} (Regular/Medium).\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab Used for body copy and descriptions.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Technical (Data):} {\b JetBrains Mono}.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab Used for hashes, addresses, and agent terminal logs.\sa180\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 {\b 4. Iconography}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The {\b Atomic Neuron} icon should always maintain its clear geometric proportions. - The outer ring represents the network (Algorand). - The inner synapse represents the core intelligence. - The central point represents the singularity of the agent.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 {\b 4.1 $CORTEX Token Icon}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The token icon uses a {\b Neural Blue gradient} (#007AFF to #003F7F) with a simplified white Atomic Neuron. It should be used for all on-chain metadata and wallet displays.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 {\b 4.2 Twitter/X Profile Picture}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The PFP uses the high-contrast {\b Obsidian background} (#050505) with the full-glow Atomic Neuron. This projects a sense of deep-infrastructure stability and \u8220"Always Online\u8221" autonomy.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 {\b 5. Usage Rules}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Always maintain a clear margin around the logo (min 20% of width).\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Do not distort the aspect ratio.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Preferred background is Obsidian (#050505) or deep gradients.\sa180\par}
